fullTest <- read.csv("../Cleaning/output/fullTest.csv")
fullTrain <- read.csv("../Cleaning/output/fullTrain.csv")

traitsFreqs <- read.csv("../Cleaning/output/traitFreqOverUnder.csv")

uSubs <- unique(fullTest$subID)

indDiffs <- fullTest[!duplicated(fullTest$subID),]

allPosCents <- read.csv("/Volumes/GoogleDrive/My Drive/Volumes/Research Project/Trait Network_Behaviral/generating network/output/allPosCents.csv")
fullTest$ingChoiceN <- as.factor(fullTest$ingChoiceN)
fullTest$novel <- as.factor(fullTest$novel)
fullTest$selfResp.Z <- scale(fullTest$selfResp)
fullTest$SE.Z <- scale(fullTest$SE)
fullTest$iSE.Z <- scale(fullTest$iSE)
fullTest$oSE.Z <- scale(fullTest$oSE)
fullTest$predicted.Z <- scale(fullTest$predicted)
fullTest$slope.Z <- scale(fullTest$slope)
fullTest$entropy.Z <- scale(fullTest$entropy)
fullTest$WSR.Z <- scale(fullTest$WSR)
fullTest$neighAveOutSE.Z <- scale(fullTest$neighAveOutSE)
fullTest$neighAveAllSE.Z <- scale(fullTest$neighAveAllSE)
fullTest$neighAveInSE.Z <- scale(fullTest$neighAveInSE)
fullTest$evalLOO.Z <- scale(fullTest$evalLOO)
fullTest$propCorrInLOO.Z <- scale(fullTest$propCorrInLOO)
fullTest$propCorrOutLOO.Z <- scale(fullTest$propCorrOutLOO)
#fullTest$propCorr.Z <- scale(fullTest$propCorr)
fullTest$desirability.Z <- scale(fullTest$desirability)
fullTest$er.Z <- scale(fullTest$er)
fullTest$novel <- as.factor(fullTest$novel)
levels(fullTest$novel) <- list("Trained"  = "0", "Held Out" = "1")

fullTest$outgroup <- as.factor(fullTest$outgroup)
fullTest$outgroup <- relevel(fullTest$outgroup,"Not UCR")
PCA<- prcomp(na.omit(fullTest[c("predicted","neighAveOutSE")]),
                center = TRUE,
                scale. = TRUE)
fullTest$PCA[!is.na(fullTest$predicted) & !is.na(fullTest$neighAveOutSE)] <- PCA$x[,1]
propMatrix <- matrix(nrow=148,ncol=7)
for(i in 1:148){
    traitDf <- subset(fullTest, Idx==i)
    test <- t.test(as.numeric(traitDf$ingChoiceN)-1, mu=.50)
    propMatrix[i, ] <- c(i, test$statistic, test$p.value, test$conf.int, test$estimate, test$parameter)
}
colnames(propMatrix) <- c("Idx", "stat", "p", "LCI", "UCI", "est", "param")
propMatrix <- as.data.frame(propMatrix)
propMatrix$trait <- traitsFreqs$trait[1:148]
propMatrix <- propMatrix[order(propMatrix$p),]

m <- glmer( ingChoiceN ~ desirability.Z +  ( desirability.Z  | subID) + ( 1 | trait), data = fullTest, family = binomial, control = glmerControl(optimizer = \bobyqa\,
                                    optCtrl = list(maxfun = 100000)),
    nAGQ = 1)
summary(m)

m <- glmer( ingChoiceN ~ desirability.Z * outgroup +  ( desirability.Z  | subID) + ( 1 | trait), data = fullTest, family = binomial, control = glmerControl(optimizer = \bobyqa\,
                                    optCtrl = list(maxfun = 100000)),
    nAGQ = 1)

# Replication of prior self-anchoring findings: Self-evaluations predicting ingroup evaluations

## No covariates


<!-- rnb-text-end -->


<!-- rnb-chunk-begin -->


<!-- rnb-source-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYGBgclxuYGBgclxubSA8LSBnbG1lciggaW5nQ2hvaWNlTiB+IHNlbGZSZXNwLlogICsgICggc2VsZlJlc3AuWiB8IHN1YklEKSArICggMSB8IHRyYWl0KSwgZGF0YSA9IGZ1bGxUZXN0LCBmYW1pbHkgPSBiaW5vbWlhbCwgY29udHJvbCA9IGdsbWVyQ29udHJvbChvcHRpbWl6ZXIgPSBcXGJvYnlxYVxcLFxuICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgb3B0Q3RybCA9IGxpc3QobWF4ZnVuID0gMTAwMDAwKSksXG4gICAgbkFHUSA9IDEpXG5zdW1tYXJ5KG0pXG5gYGBcbmBgYCJ9 -->

```r
```r
m <- glmer( ingChoiceN ~ selfResp.Z  +  ( selfResp.Z | subID) + ( 1 | trait), data = fullTest, family = binomial, control = glmerControl(optimizer = \bobyqa\,
                                    optCtrl = list(maxfun = 100000)),
    nAGQ = 1)
summary(m)

## With desirability covariates and differences with outgroup

Self-evaluations are more predictive of ingroup choices for negation and least predictive for CSU LA.

```r
```r
m <- glmer( ingChoiceN ~ selfResp.Z * outgroup + desirability.Z +  ( selfResp.Z | subID) + ( 1 | trait), data = fullTest, family = binomial, control = glmerControl(optimizer = \bobyqa\,
                                    optCtrl = list(maxfun = 100000)),
    nAGQ = 1)
summary(m)

<!-- rnb-source-end -->

```r
```r
m <- glmer( ingChoiceN ~ evalLOO.Z + desirability.Z + ( evalLOO.Z | subID) + ( 1 | trait), data = fullTest, family = binomial, control = glmerControl(optimizer = \bobyqa\,
                                    optCtrl = list(maxfun = 100000)),
    nAGQ = 1)
summary(m)
tidy(m,conf.int=TRUE,exponentiate=TRUE,effects=\fixed\)
r2beta(m)
ggpredict(m, c(\evalLOO.Z\)) %>% plot(show.title=F) + xlab(\Leave-One-Out Self-Descriptiveness\) + ylab(\Likelihood of Ingroup Choice\) + jtools::theme_apa()

# Do cross-validated similarity*self-evaluation predictions predict ingroup choices? 

## No covariates


<!-- rnb-text-end -->


<!-- rnb-chunk-begin -->


<!-- rnb-source-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYGBgclxuYGBgclxubSA8LSBnbG1lciggaW5nQ2hvaWNlTiB+IHByZWRpY3RlZC5aKm91dGdyb3VwICsgKCBwcmVkaWN0ZWQuWiB8IHN1YklEKSArICgxIHwgdHJhaXQpLCBkYXRhID0gZnVsbFRlc3QsIGZhbWlseSA9IGJpbm9taWFsLCBjb250cm9sID0gZ2xtZXJDb250cm9sKG9wdGltaXplciA9IFxcYm9ieXFhXFwsXG4gICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICBvcHRDdHJsID0gbGlzdChtYXhmdW4gPSAxMDAwMDApKSxcbiAgICBuQUdRID0gMSlcbnN1bW1hcnkobSlcbmdncHJlZGljdChtLCBjKFxccHJlZGljdGVkLlpcXCxcXG91dGdyb3VwXFwpKSAlPiUgcGxvdCgpXG5gYGBcbmBgYCJ9 -->

```r
```r
m <- glmer( ingChoiceN ~ predicted.Z*outgroup + ( predicted.Z | subID) + (1 | trait), data = fullTest, family = binomial, control = glmerControl(optimizer = \bobyqa\,
                                    optCtrl = list(maxfun = 100000)),
    nAGQ = 1)
summary(m)
ggpredict(m, c(\predicted.Z\,\outgroup\)) %>% plot()

<!-- rnb-source-end -->

<!-- rnb-chunk-end -->

# Covariates


<!-- rnb-text-end -->


<!-- rnb-chunk-begin -->


<!-- rnb-source-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYGBgclxuYGBgclxubSA8LSBnbG1lciggaW5nQ2hvaWNlTiB+IHByZWRpY3RlZC5aICsgcHJvcENvcnJJbkxPTy5aICsgZGVzaXJhYmlsaXR5LlogKyAoIHByZWRpY3RlZC5aIHwgc3ViSUQpICsgKDEgfCB0cmFpdCksIGRhdGEgPSBmdWxsVGVzdCwgZmFtaWx5ID0gYmlub21pYWwsIGNvbnRyb2wgPSBnbG1lckNvbnRyb2wob3B0aW1pemVyID0gXFxib2J5cWFcXCxcbiAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgIG9wdEN0cmwgPSBsaXN0KG1heGZ1biA9IDEwMDAwMCkpLFxuICAgIG5BR1EgPSAxKVxuc3VtbWFyeShtKVxudGlkeShtLGNvbmYuaW50PVRSVUUsZXhwb25lbnRpYXRlPVRSVUUsZWZmZWN0cz1cXGZpeGVkXFwpXG5yMmJldGEobSlcbmdncHJlZGljdChtLCBjKFxccHJlZGljdGVkLlpcXCkpICU+JSBwbG90KHNob3cudGl0bGU9RikgKyB4bGFiKFxcQ3Jvc3MtVmFsaWRhdGVkIFNlbGYtRGVzY3JpcHRpdmVuZXNzIFByZWRpY3Rpb25zXFwpICsgeWxhYihcXExpa2VsaWhvb2Qgb2YgSW5ncm91cCBDaG9pY2VcXCkgKyBqdG9vbHM6OnRoZW1lX2FwYSgpXG4jZ2dzYXZlKFxcfi9Eb2N1bWVudHMvVUMgUml2ZXJzaWRlL1N0dWRpZXMvU2VsZi1BbmNob3JpbmcvRmlndXJlcy9DVnByZWRpY3Rpb24udGlmZlxcLGRwaT02MDApXG5gYGBcbmBgYCJ9 -->

```r
```r
m <- glmer( ingChoiceN ~ predicted.Z + propCorrInLOO.Z + desirability.Z + ( predicted.Z | subID) + (1 | trait), data = fullTest, family = binomial, control = glmerControl(optimizer = \bobyqa\,
                                    optCtrl = list(maxfun = 100000)),
    nAGQ = 1)
summary(m)
tidy(m,conf.int=TRUE,exponentiate=TRUE,effects=\fixed\)
r2beta(m)
ggpredict(m, c(\predicted.Z\)) %>% plot(show.title=F) + xlab(\Cross-Validated Self-Descriptiveness Predictions\) + ylab(\Likelihood of Ingroup Choice\) + jtools::theme_apa()

<!-- rnb-chunk-begin -->


<!-- rnb-source-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYGBgclxuYGBgclxubSA8LSBnbG1lciggaW5nQ2hvaWNlTiB+IHNjYWxlKHNsb3BlKSArIHNlbGZSZXNwLlogICsgKCBzY2FsZShzbG9wZSkgKyBzZWxmUmVzcC5aIHwgc3ViSUQpICsgKDEgfCB0cmFpdCksIGRhdGEgPSBmdWxsVGVzdCwgZmFtaWx5ID0gYmlub21pYWwsIGNvbnRyb2wgPSBnbG1lckNvbnRyb2wob3B0aW1pemVyID0gXFxib2J5cWFcXCxcbiAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgIG9wdEN0cmwgPSBsaXN0KG1heGZ1biA9IDEwMDAwMCkpLFxuICAgIG5BR1EgPSAxKVxuc3VtbWFyeShtKVxudGlkeShtLGNvbmYuaW50PVRSVUUsZXhwb25lbnRpYXRlPVRSVUUsZWZmZWN0cz1cXGZpeGVkXFwpXG5gYGBcbmBgYCJ9 -->

# Backwards solution: Can you predict self-evaluations from similarity to ingroup and outgroup choices?


<!-- rnb-text-end -->


<!-- rnb-chunk-begin -->


<!-- rnb-source-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYGBgclxuYGBgclxubSA8LSBsbWVyKCBzY2FsZShzZWxmUmVzcCkgfiBzY2FsZShpbkdzaW0pKm91dGdyb3VwICsgc2NhbGUob3V0R3NpbSkgKyAoICBzY2FsZShpbkdzaW0pICsgc2NhbGUob3V0R3NpbSkgfCBzdWJJRCkgKyAoMSB8IHRyYWl0KSwgZGF0YSA9IGZ1bGxUcmFpbilcbnN1bW1hcnkobSlcbnRpZHkobSxjb25mLmludD1UUlVFLGVmZmVjdHM9XFxmaXhlZFxcKVxuZ2dwcmVkaWN0KG0sIGMoXFxpbkdzaW1cXCxcXG91dGdyb3VwXFwpKSAlPiUgcGxvdChzaG93LnRpdGxlPUYpICsgeGxhYihcXFNpbWlsYXJpdHkgdG8gSW5ncm91cCBDaG9pY2VzXFwpICsgeWxhYihcXFNlbGYtRXZhbHVhdGlvblxcKSArIGp0b29sczo6dGhlbWVfYXBhKClcbmBgYFxuYGBgIn0= -->

```r
```r
m <- lmer( scale(selfResp) ~ scale(inGsim)*outgroup + scale(outGsim) + (  scale(inGsim) + scale(outGsim) | subID) + (1 | trait), data = fullTrain)
summary(m)
tidy(m,conf.int=TRUE,effects=\fixed\)
ggpredict(m, c(\inGsim\,\outgroup\)) %>% plot(show.title=F) + xlab(\Similarity to Ingroup Choices\) + ylab(\Self-Evaluation\) + jtools::theme_apa()

## Moderated by Group Homophily

People who mentally segregrate the groups also self-evaluate more similar to their later group choices.


<!-- rnb-text-end -->


<!-- rnb-chunk-begin -->


<!-- rnb-source-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYGBgclxuYGBgclxubSA8LSBsbWVyKCBzY2FsZShzZWxmUmVzcCkgfiBzY2FsZShpbkdzaW0pICogc2NhbGUoZ3JvdXBIb21vcGgpICsgc2NhbGUob3V0R3NpbSkgKyAoICBzY2FsZShpbkdzaW0pICsgc2NhbGUob3V0R3NpbSkgfCBzdWJJRCkgKyAoMSB8IHRyYWl0KSwgZGF0YSA9IGZ1bGxUcmFpbilcbnN1bW1hcnkobSlcbnRpZHkobSxjb25mLmludD1UUlVFLGVmZmVjdHM9XFxmaXhlZFxcKVxuZ2dwcmVkaWN0KG0sIGMoXFxpbkdzaW1cXCxcXGdyb3VwSG9tb3BoXFwpKSAlPiUgcGxvdChzaG93LnRpdGxlPUYpICsgeGxhYihcXFNpbWlsYXJpdHkgdG8gSW5ncm91cCBDaG9pY2VzXFwpICsgeWxhYihcXFNlbGYtRXZhbHVhdGlvblxcKSArIGp0b29sczo6dGhlbWVfYXBhKClcbmBgYFxuYGBgIn0= -->

```r
```r
m <- lmer( scale(selfResp) ~ scale(inGsim) * scale(groupHomoph) + scale(outGsim) + (  scale(inGsim) + scale(outGsim) | subID) + (1 | trait), data = fullTrain)
summary(m)
tidy(m,conf.int=TRUE,effects=\fixed\)
ggpredict(m, c(\inGsim\,\groupHomoph\)) %>% plot(show.title=F) + xlab(\Similarity to Ingroup Choices\) + ylab(\Self-Evaluation\) + jtools::theme_apa()

                                    optCtrl = list(maxfun = 100000)),
    nAGQ = 1)
summary(m)
ggpredict(m, c(\predicted.Z\, \groupHomoph\)) %>% plot()

    nAGQ = 1)
